+All existing `/file-browser/*` endpoints unchanged. No backend changes.
+
+### Multi-Instance / Factory Pattern
+
+The file browser supports multiple independent instances on the same page. Each instance gets its own DOM tree, state, config, and public API.
+
+#### How it works
+
+1. `interface.html` contains a `<template id="file-browser-modal-template">` with all file browser HTML. Elements inside use `data-fb-key="keyName"` attributes instead of static IDs.
+2. `createFileBrowser(instanceId, initialCfg)` clones the template, walks all `[data-fb-key]` elements, and assigns each a concrete ID: `{instanceId}-{keyName}`.
+3. The cloned DOM is appended to `<body>`. The returned API object's internal `_$('keyName')` helper resolves to `$('#{instanceId}-{keyName}')`, so each instance targets only its own elements.
+4. Each instance has its own `state` object and `_config`, completely isolated from other instances.
+
+#### Creating instances
+
+```javascript
+// Default Settings instance (created automatically on DOM ready)
+// window.FileBrowserManager = createFileBrowser('fb');
+// Element IDs: fb-modal, fb-tree, fb-address-bar, ...
+
+// Global Docs instance (created by GlobalDocsManager)
+var gdocsBrowser = createFileBrowser('global-docs-fb', {
+    rootPath: 'storage/global_docs/user123/',
+    onMove: function(src, dest, done) {
+        // custom move logic for global docs
+        $.post('/global_docs/move', { src: src, dest: dest }, function() {
+            done(null);
+        }).fail(function() { done('Move failed'); });
+    },
+    onDelete: function(path, done) {
+        $.post('/global_docs/delete', { path: path }, function() {
+            done(null);
+        }).fail(function() { done('Delete failed'); });
+    }
+});
+gdocsBrowser.init();
+gdocsBrowser.open();
+// Element IDs: global-docs-fb-modal, global-docs-fb-tree, ...
+
+// Any number of additional instances
+var uploadBrowser = createFileBrowser('upload-fb', {
+    rootPath: 'uploads/',
+    readOnly: true,
+    showEditor: false
+});
+uploadBrowser.init();
+```
+
+#### Instance isolation
+
+Each instance is fully independent:
+- Separate DOM (cloned from template, unique IDs per instance)
+- Separate `state` (expanded dirs, current file, dirty flag, etc.)
+- Separate `_config` (endpoints, callbacks, behavior flags)
+- Opening or closing one instance doesn't affect another
+- `window.FileBrowserManager` (the `'fb'` instance) continues to work exactly as before for all existing code
+
+#### Real-world usage: GlobalDocsManager
+
+In `interface/global-docs-manager.js`, the Global Docs feature creates its own file browser:
+
+```javascript
+GlobalDocsManager._fileBrowser = createFileBrowser('global-docs-fb', {
+    rootPath: GlobalDocsManager._folderRoot,
+    onMove: function(src, dest, done) { /* folder API */ },
+    onDelete: function(path, done) { /* folder API */ }
+});
+```
+
+This instance is completely independent from the Settings file browser. Both can be open simultaneously without conflicts.
 
